name: Código Morsa [walrus code. morse pun]
description: a pun on the spanish word for walrus [morsa]. a walrus using morse code. inspired by johnny cash who was a WW2 morse code interceptor. the message the walrus is sending is S-H-H-H-! shhh! "What hath GOD wrought" was the first message sent in morse code, so i did a little change to dog bought to keep the fun rolling. the technique simulates acrilic paint on pixels. the background is the morse code alphabet @azteco_producciones
